bob dylan & the poetry of the blues an evening with writer michael gray bob dylan & the poetry of the blues an evening with writer michael gray facebook twitter email print add to calendar michael gray is the author of the award winning bob dylan encyclopedia and song & dance man iii the art of bob dylan definitive studies of dylan's 50 year body of work he will play memorable recordings and screen rare footage to argue for the key role of the blues as an inspiration for dylan's music and lyrics when thursday february 24 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where building 260 room 113 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading music film humanities arts sponsor african & african american studies american studies program contact 650 725 1477 monica moore stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 264 26443 last modified january 18 2011
